<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: WEEK OF CAMP OFFERED TO LOW-INCOME YOUTHS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hollywood youngsters from low-income families will have a chance to attend 
Scout camp for a week this summer as part of a program sponsored by the 
Hollywood Sentinels Neighborhood Watch organization. 
</P>
<P>
The Sentinels, a crime-watch group established in 1988, sponsors a local Boy 
Scout and Girl Scout troop to provide area children with activities designed to 
keep them out of trouble and away from gangs. 
</P>
<P>
Both troops feature weekly meetings and monthly outings for all Scouts, who 
come from the DeLongpre Park area. 
</P>
<P>
This summer, the Sentinels have planned two outings. The Boy Scouts will 
participate in a one-week session at the Los Angeles Council Boy Scouts' Lake 
Arrowhead camps. Also, the Boy Scouts and Girl Scouts will participate in a 
one-week excursion to the Los Angeles Area Council's Cabrillo Beach Youth 
Waterfront Sports Center. For more information, call Fares Wehbe at (213) 
465-6503. 
</P>
</TEXT>
