<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MAN TO STAND TRIAL IN ATTACK WITH ACID 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Hacienda Heights man was ordered Monday to stand trial for allegedly blinding 
and disfiguring a Glendale woman by throwing acid in her face. 
</P>
<P>
After a two-day preliminary hearing, a Glendale Municipal Court judge ordered 
Emad Fawzi Kalta, 20, to be arraigned on July 10 in Pasadena Superior Court. 
</P>
<P>
Kalta is charged with aggravated mayhem, mayhem resulting in great bodily 
injury and assault with a caustic chemical. If convicted, he could be sentenced 
to life in prison without possibility of parole. 
</P>
<P>
Prosecutors contend that Kalta approached Shushan Eloyan, 23, last July on 
Adams Street and asked her a question. When she turned to respond, Kalta 
allegedly threw a jar of nitric acid in Eloyan's face. Prosecutors have said 
the attack may have been an act of vengeance triggered by a dispute between 
members of the victim's family. 
</P>
<P>
Several witnesses testified during the hearing that they saw Kalta carrying a 
jar of liquid and running toward Eloyan. A fingerprint analyst testified that 
Kalta's fingerprints were found on the jar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
