<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
New Kid in the Hospital: A member of the New Kids on the Block singing group 
was listed in stable condition Monday after suffering several injuries when he 
fell on stage during the grand finale of the group's concert in Saratoga 
Springs, N.Y. Donnie Wahlberg, 20, suffered bruises to his chest and cuts to 
his arms and his mouth during Sunday night's concert at Saratoga Raceway. He 
was admitted to Saratoga Hospital at 1:10 a.m. Monday and was taken to 
intensive care for "his privacy and protection," said Helen Edelman, director 
of community relations for the hospital. 
</P>
<P>
He was being guarded by his personal bodyguard, who is only known as "Robo," 
she said. Wahlberg had to have stitches in his lower lip, and was having 
trouble talking Monday morning, Edelman said. At least 100 teen-age girls 
crowded the lobby of the hospital, and scores of cards and flowers from 
well-wishing fans filled the hospital. The concert was the second of the 
group's "Summer Magic" tour. Officials said that they did not know when 
Wahlberg would be released, or if the injury would affect the group's scheduled 
performance tonight in Auburn Hills, Mich. The New Kids' new album, "Step By 
Step" is currently No. 1 on the charts. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Wahlberg 
</P>
