<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: PEOPLE WATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Melina Mercouri for Mayor: Melina Mercouri, Greece's popular actress turned 
fiery socialist politician, will seek to become mayor of Athens in municipal 
elections in October. The Panhellenic Socialist Movement (PASOK), which was 
defeated in a general election last June after eight years in power, has chosen 
Mercouri as its candidate against the ruling New Democracy Party. 
</P>
<P>
"Mercouri is probably the only person in PASOK popular enough to attract even 
conservative voters. If she wins the election, it could mean a new start for 
our party," a senior PASOK official said. Mercouri, 65, served as culture 
minister from 1981 until 1989 in the government of former Prime Minister 
Andreas Papandreou and led a campaign to promote Athens as host for the 1996 
Olympic Games. She is best known for her role as a prostitute in the 1960 film 
"Never on Sunday," for which she won an Oscar nomination. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
