The Federal Resolution Trust Corp. decided Friday to pay off customers with 
insured deposits at Wilshire Federal Savings after failing to find a buyer for 
the Los Angeles Thrift. 
</P>
<P>
The thrift, seized by regulators in January, had nearly $79 million in deposits 
in 1,500 accounts. 
</P>
