<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: BISHOP INC. RECEIVES $1.5-MILLION LINE OF CREDIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bishop Inc., an Agoura Hills supplier of design and engineering equipment, said 
it obtained a $1.5-million line of credit from CoastFed Business Credit Corp. 
</P>
<P>
The funding will be used to "maximize our strong working-capital position," 
which will help the company expand, President John J. Theiss said in a 
statement. 
</P>
<P>
Bishop has struggled in recent years and is now restructuring. In the six 
months that ended March 31, it lost $361,000 on revenue of $4.95 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
