<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: ATI MEDICAL TO EXPAND TO RESIDENTIAL MARKET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATI Medical, a Glendale-based company that rents medical equipment to 
hospitals, said it plans to also begin renting products to the residential 
health-care market. 
</P>
<P>
In making the announcement at ATI's annual meeting, President Paul E. Stevenson 
said the portion of the residential market in which ATI will compete has annual 
revenue of about $3 billion, compared with $250 million for the hospital market 
in which ATI now vies. 
</P>
<P>
ATI said it is arranging relationships with residential health-care dealers in 
120 U.S. cities that would have exclusive rights to ATI's equipment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
