<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jeffrey A. Perlman and Barbie Ludovise 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HURDLERS: Danny Harris and Edwin Moses are now neighbors. . . . Moses, of 
Newport Beach, holds the world record in the intermediate hurdles, and Harris, 
his hottest challenger, is the man who broke Moses' nearly 10-year string of 
victories in 1987. . . . Harris has moved from Los Angeles to Irvine (C12) and 
is training on the UCI track, where Moses has been seen working out. . . . It's 
quiet here, Harris says, and a relief from L.A. traffic and smog. Jeffrey A. 
Perlman and Barbie Ludovise 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
