NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dr. Marvin Burns, an All-American water polo and swimming at USC and a two-time 
Olympian, died Sunday of cancer. 
</P>
<P>
He was 61. 
</P>
<P>
Burns attended USC from 1948-52 and was on the U.S. Olympic water polo teams in 
1952 and 1960. 
</P>
<P>
Burns was a lifetime resident of Fullerton. He attended Fullerton High School 
and Fullerton College. 
</P>
<P>
Services for Burns will be Wednesday at Emanuel Episcopal Church in Fullerton. 
</P>
