<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: SCIENCE/TECHNOLOGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Dean Takahashi, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
To Japan Market: AST Research Inc. of Irvine says it will manufacture the first 
1,000 personal computers that it plans to market in Japan at its Fountain 
Valley plant, said Joel Don, a company spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
The computers, which are compatible with both International Business Machines 
Corp. personal computers and the NEC Corp. standard machines that dominate the 
Japanese PC market, will be sent to a variety of large Japanese corporations 
for demonstration and testing purposes, Don said. 
</P>
<P>
The company has yet to work out a distribution agreement for mass marketing the 
computers in Japan, Don said. 
</P>
