<P>
U.S. OFFICIAL IN CHINA FOR TALKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FROM TIMES WIRE SERVICES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BEIJING 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A senior U.S. official arrived in Beijing today for talks with Chinese 
officials, one day after a dissident scientist was allowed to leave the 
American Embassy where he had sheltered for more than a year. 
</P>
<P>
Desaix Anderson, deputy assistant secretary of state, will hold talks with 
Foreign Ministry officials on Sino-American relations and other issues during 
his stay of about five days, U.S. Embassy officials said. 
</P>
<P>
He is the most senior U.S. official to visit China since National Security 
Adviser Brent Scowcroft made a highly controversial visit in December. 
</P>
<P>
His visit follows by one day the release of Fang Lizhi and his wife, Li 
Shuxian. American officials called the timing of the visit coincidental. 
</P>
