<P>
'PEAKS' ACTOR FACES DRUG COUNT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FROM TIMES WIRE SERVICES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
EGREMONT, Mass. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Michael J. Anderson, who danced and babbled in backward English during a dream 
sequence on ABC's "Twin Peaks," has been arrested on a charge of hashish 
possession. 
</P>
<P>
The 3-foot-7 actor was arrested Monday after a car in which he was a passenger 
was stopped for a bent license plate, police said. Anderson, 36, was freed on 
bail. He is in the area for rehearsal of a play to open in August in 
Stockbridge. 
</P>
</TEXT>
