<HEADLINE>
<P>
NAMES IN THE NEWS; 
</P>
<P>
GALA TO OPEN GARSON CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FROM TIMES WIRE SERVICES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANTE FE, N.M. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A gala tribute to Greer Garson will be held at New Mexico's College of Santa Fe 
Oct. 20 for the opening of the Greer Garson Communications Center and Studios. 
</P>
<P>
The English-born Academy Award winner, who makes her home in Santa Fe, made the 
project possible by her financial gift to the college more than a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
The communications center and studios are the latest in a list of contributions 
to the college by Garson and her late husband, E. E. (Buddy) Fogelson. The 
Garson Studios provides 22,000 square feet of filming space, the largest such 
film-TV studio facility in New Mexico. 
</P>
</TEXT>
