NAMES IN THE NEWS; 
</P>
<P>
MAYNARD JACKSON III DOING TIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FROM TIMES WIRE SERVICES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ATLANTA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The 19-year-old son of Mayor Maynard Jackson apologized for knocking down his 
girlfriend on a street, but it wasn't enough to keep him out of jail. 
</P>
<P>
Municipal Judge Harvey Moskowitz on Monday upheld a charge of disorderly 
conduct and ordered Maynard Jackson III to complete a 45-day sentence. 
</P>
<P>
Jackson has been in jail since soon after the June 18 incident involving Maria 
Norma Duarte, 30. He was charged with pushing her to the ground after trying to 
grab her can of Mace. It was his third arrest this year. "I know I was wrong," 
he told the judge. "I should have held back my temper." 
</P>
</TEXT>
