<HEADLINE>
<P>
SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
KELLY NAMED YEAR'S TOP PLAYER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FROM TIMES WIRE SERVICES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ST. LOUIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Arizona State center fielder Mike Kelly has been named The Sporting News' 
college baseball player of the year, the publication said today. 
</P>
<P>
Kelly is the ninth player from Arizona State to be selected for the award. A 
sophomore, he hit .376 with 21 home runs, 82 RBIs and 230 stolen bases this 
season. 
</P>
<P>
Chal Port of The Citadel was selected the college baseball coach of the year. 
His team posted a school-record 46 victories, including a winning streak of 26 
games. 
</P>
<P>
The Citadel captured the Atlantic Region championship and earned a berth in the 
College World Series, its first in Port's 26-year tenure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
