<HEADLINE>
<P>
SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
TARPLEY'S DWI HEARING DELAYED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FROM TIMES WIRE SERVICES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DALLAS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dallas Mavericks forward Roy Tarpley's on-again, off-again court appearance on 
a DWI charge is off again. 
</P>
<P>
A hearing had been scheduled Monday on the DWI and resisting arrest charges, 
after several previous postponements. 
</P>
<P>
Tarpley's attorney, Jay Ethington, said the pretrial hearing is rescheduled for 
Sept. 7. The trial is scheduled for Sept. 10 and should take about a week, he 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The Mavericks standout was arrested Nov. 15 on a north Dallas freeway after 
officers spotted him driving his car too close to another vehicle. 
</P>
<P>
The arrest resulted in his suspension for 33 games. He was reinstated Jan. 22. 
</P>
<P>
Tarpley has twice been treated for drug and alcohol abuse. 
</P>
</TEXT>
