<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANGRY STEFFI MAY LEAVE GERMANY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BONN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Reigning Wimbledon tennis champion Steffi Graf says she is considering moving 
to the United States and boycotting events in West Germany because of lurid 
newspaper headlines linking her father to a topless model. 
</P>
<P>
"I'm sorry to have to say this, but I hate these people," the No. 1-ranked 
women's tennis player was quoted as saying in the latest edition of the West 
German news magazine Stern. 
</P>
<P>
"I will never stop hating these people who want to destroy my family just to 
boost the circulation of their newspapers," Graf added. 
</P>
<P>
West German tabloid newspapers have splashed stories of her father Peter, 52, 
and nude model Nicole Meissner, 22, over their front pages, complete with 
eye-catching photographs of the unclad woman. 
</P>
<P>
In the Stern interview, Graf attributed her losses in the French and German 
Open tournaments to anxiety over the stories. 
</P>
<P>
"I don't want to give up tennis . . . but I might go to America and temporarily 
not play in Germany if the newspapers hurt me and my family again in the future 
with their headlines," she said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Graf, angry at press, advanced at Wimbledon. Reuters 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
