<HEADLINE>
<P>
OILERS' ROZIER IS TARGET OF SECOND PATERNITY SUIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HOUSTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Houston Oilers running back Mike Rozier has been named in a paternity suit for 
the second time in a month by women who each contend he is the father of their 
unborn child. 
</P>
<P>
The latest suit was filed Monday by Rita Baldwin, 25, who contends Rozier is 
the father of her baby, according to lawyer Glenn Lilly, who also represents 
Pamela Gobert, 23, who filed a paternity suit against Rozier earlier this 
month. 
</P>
<P>
Baldwin, an unemployed student in Dickinson, said in the suit filed in Harris 
County Family District Court that she is expecting a baby in September. 
</P>
<P>
Gobert is four months' pregnant, Lilly said. 
</P>
<P>
Both women are seeking medical costs and child support for their children, he 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Rozier has 21 days to respond to Baldwin's suit and until July 16 to respond to 
Gobert's petition. If he contests fatherhood of either child, Lilly will ask 
the court to order medical tests to determine paternity. 
</P>
<P>
Rozier so far has paid for the initial doctor's visits for both the women, 
Lilly said. 
</P>
<P>
Baldwin apparently was unaware of Rozier's relationship with Gobert, Lilly 
said. He described the Baldwin-Rozier relationship as "girlfriend on and off 
for some time." 
</P>
<P>
"Rita (Baldwin) obviously feels lied to and deceived by Mike Rozier," the 
lawyer said. 
</P>
<P>
Rozier signed a one-year contract with the Oilers last week. The contract 
includes several lucrative incentive bonuses and is expected to match the 
previous year's $625,000 base salary and $25,000 signing bonus. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Mike Rozier 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
